Temeke District Commissioner,  Mr Godwin Gondwe has ordered the arrest and detention of the operators  and supervisors  of the chemical storage warehouse at Kisewe area  in Dar es Salaam region  after learning that the facility  wasn’t registered. Mr Gondwe has issued the directive today, during the ongoing inspection of chemical storage warehouses in Temeke District, accompanied by officials from the Government Chemist Laboratory Authority, National Environment Management Council (NEMC),  Tanzania Bureau of Standards (TBS) and the District Defense and Security Committee. Despite the warehouse being unregistered, the District Commissioner  revealed that there were various expired chemicals that were repackaged into new bags and then taken  to the market for sale. The DC ordered that warehouse  be placed under close monitoring before  further measures are instituted, including destroying the chemicals under  government supervision.